                 THE PUZZLE FACTORY ANNOUNCES

                          ORIGINS

The Puzzle Factory, Inc. has released Origins, a dedicated data base for
keeping track of genealogical information.  It will support databases of
over 6 million individuals.  The user interface is designed to be both
easy to use and very powerful.  Origins will correctly handle multiple
marriages, step-children, unmarried parents, and other difficult
situations that some programs refuse to allow.  Lists Persons, Marriages,
Parent/Child Index, Ahnentafel (direct ancestors), and Soundex (grouping
surnames by similar pronunciation).  Generates reports on Persons, Family
Group sheets, Pedigree Charts, Descendants Charts, and Tiny-Tafel
(a summary of your surnames).

Features include:  Automatically call your ARexx-compatible editor to
create Source and Note files.  These files may also be written and
displayed in hypertext format.

* Search on any combination of fields or by Soundex codes.

* Context-sensitive hypertext help is built in.

* Support for IFF files.  Pictures of individuals, marriages,
  baptisms, and family groups may be displayed instantly.

* Import and export data between Origins and other
  genealogical programs using the standard GEDCOM file format.

* Generate Tiny-Tafel listings for use with the Tafel Matching
  System.

* Many useful ARexx functions are included.
      
A single floppy data disk will hold approximately 2000 person and
500 marriage records.  Origins is not LDS compatible.

Origins requires V1.3 or later of the Amiga OS, at least 1 megabyte
of ram, and hard disk or 2 floppy drives minimum configuration.
